traffic_visible_response: Chiang Kai-shek was known for being a Chinese military and political leader who led the Kuomintang (Chinese Nationalist Party) for five decades [[1]]. He was the leader of the Nationalist Party in China, fought against the Communist Party in the Chinese Civil War, and also against Japan in World War II [[2]]. Additionally, he joined the Chinese Nationalist Party (Kuomintang, or KMT) in 1918 and became one of the most influential world figures of the twentieth century as the leader of the Kuomintang, the Nationalist movement in China, by 1928 [[3]].
